                <h1>Meaning of the Statue of Liberty: A Symbol of Freedom</h1>
                <p>The Statue of Liberty symbolizes freedom, democracy, and hope. Gifted by France to the United States in 1886, it stands as a welcoming beacon to immigrants arriving in New York City. This iconic monument embodies the spirit of liberty and serves as a reminder of the enduring values of equality and opportunity, inspiring generations worldwide.</p>
